			<div class="content" id="post-content-1393698">
									

<p>I don't believe that you can generally apply a strict interpretation to any story that's ambiguous, but I'm still curious as to how obvious I made the hints, and to what people think of it, so I offer the following questions for thought and discussion:</p>
<p>1) Is he right (in his conclusion in Part 12)?<br />
2) What will happen if his plan succeeds and he reaches the city?</p>
<p>(In answering them, if it would spoil something to a person who hasn't read the story already, use this:</p>
