<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Show</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Hide</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>1) Well, There is No Canon, so he might. On the other hand he may just be dellusional, guess we'll never know.<br />
I'm seriously thinkig, that this should be considered SCP-001 proposal.<br />
2) The Foundation would cover it up, depending obviously on what would be in the briefcase. Then again, they have ways of making stuff disappear. It's kind of depressing, really. Knowing that one man could never dismantle such an organisation, be it the Foundation, or anything else.</p>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Hide</a></div>
</div>
</div>
<br />
That being said it's a very decent tale, with a very interesting twist.<br />
Upvoted
<p>EDIT: I also love the touch with 13 parts, corresponding with the number of O5s.<br />
Or am I wrong? I think there are 13 of them.</p>

